      "content": "The myth of meritocracy is a convenient fiction used to mask structural oppression, suggesting that current wealth is solely the result of individual effort. In reality, starting lines are drastically unequal due to generations of discriminatory policies, meaning \"earning\" is often just the successful navigation of inherited privilege. Restorative justice demands we acknowledge that the playing field was rigged from the start, making the concept of pure merit irrelevant until material imbalances are corrected. Therefore, wealth redistribution is the practical application of acknowledging historical injustice.",
